---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | Sol Village">
	<main class="page">
		<section class="privacy-content">
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p class="last-updated">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
				<p>
					Sol Village ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. 
					This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website 
					or use our services. This policy complies with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) and California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA).
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
				
				<h3>2.1 Personal Information</h3>
				<p>We may collect the following categories of personal information:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Identifiers:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, postal address</li>
					<li><strong>Personal Information Categories:</strong> Age, gender, family status, employment information</li>
					<li><strong>Commercial Information:</strong> Records of products or services purchased, obtained, or considered</li>
					<li><strong>Internet Activity:</strong> Browsing history, search history, information regarding your interaction with our website</li>
					<li><strong>Geolocation Data:</strong> Physical location or movements</li>
					<li><strong>Sensory Data:</strong> Audio, electronic, visual, or similar information</li>
					<li><strong>Professional Information:</strong> Employment history, professional qualifications</li>
					<li><strong>Education Information:</strong> Educational background and qualifications</li>
				</ul>

				<h3>2.2 How We Collect Information</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>Directly from you when you fill out forms on our website</li>
					<li>Through your interactions with our website and services</li>
					<li>From third-party sources, such as social media platforms</li>
					<li>Through cookies and similar tracking technologies</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
				<p>We use your personal information for the following business purposes:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>To provide and maintain our services</li>
					<li>To process your interest list applications</li>
					<li>To communicate with you about Sol Village updates and opportunities</li>
					<li>To improve our website and services</li>
					<li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
					<li>To protect our rights and prevent fraud</li>
					<li>To conduct research and analytics</li>
					<li>To send you marketing communications (with your consent)</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>4. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
				<p>We may share your personal information in the following circumstances:</p>
				
				<h3>4.1 Service Providers</h3>
				<p>We may share your information with third-party service providers who assist us in operating our website and providing our services, including:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Customer relationship management (CRM) systems</li>
					<li>Email marketing platforms</li>
					<li>Website analytics providers</li>
					<li>Payment processors</li>
				</ul>

				<h3>4.2 Legal Requirements</h3>
				<p>We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.</p>

				<h3>4.3 Business Transfers</h3>
				<p>In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.</p>

				<h3>4.4 Consent</h3>
				<p>We may share your information with your explicit consent for specific purposes.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>5. Your California Privacy Rights</h2>
				<p>If you are a California resident, you have the following rights under CCPA and CPRA:</p>
				
				<h3>5.1 Right to Know</h3>
				<p>You have the right to know what personal information we collect, use, disclose, and sell about you.</p>

				<h3>5.2 Right to Delete</h3>
				<p>You have the right to request that we delete your personal information, subject to certain exceptions.</p>

				<h3>5.3 Right to Correct</h3>
				<p>You have the right to request that we correct inaccurate personal information about you.</p>

				<h3>5.4 Right to Opt-Out</h3>
				<p>You have the right to opt-out of the sale or sharing of your personal information for cross-context behavioral advertising.</p>

				<h3>5.5 Right to Limit Sensitive Personal Information</h3>
				<p>You have the right to limit the use and disclosure of sensitive personal information.</p>

				<h3>5.6 Right to Non-Discrimination</h3>
				<p>We will not discriminate against you for exercising your privacy rights.</p>

				<h3>5.7 How to Exercise Your Rights</h3>
				<p>To exercise your rights, please contact us at:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Email: <a href="mailto:travis@sollearning.com">travis@sollearning.com</a></li>
				</ul>
				<p>We will respond to your request within 45 days of receipt.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>6. Data Security</h2>
				<p>
					We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against 
					unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet 
					or electronic storage is 100% secure.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
				<p>
					We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, 
					unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. When we no longer need your personal information, 
					we will securely delete or anonymize it.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>8. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
				<p>
					We use minimal cookies and tracking technologies on our website:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> We use basic cookies necessary for website functionality and form processing</li>
					<li><strong>Google Fonts:</strong> We load fonts from Google Fonts, which may set cookies for font optimization</li>
					<li><strong>No Analytics:</strong> We do not currently use Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, or other tracking tools</li>
					<li><strong>No Advertising:</strong> We do not use advertising cookies or third-party marketing trackers</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					You can control cookie settings through your browser preferences. Most browsers allow you to refuse cookies or 
					delete them after your visit. However, disabling cookies may affect website functionality.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
				<p>
					Our services are not directed to children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information 
					from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, 
					please contact us immediately.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>10. Third-Party Links</h2>
				<p>
					Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content 
					of these third-party sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>11. International Data Transfers</h2>
				<p>
					If you are accessing our services from outside the United States, please be aware that your information may be 
					transferred to, stored, and processed in the United States where our servers are located.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
				<p>
					We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy 
					on this page and updating the "Last updated" date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="privacy-section">
				<h2>13. Contact Information</h2>
				<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Email: <a href="mailto:travis@sollearning.com">travis@sollearning.com</a></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.page {
		min-height: 100vh;
		padding: 120px clamp(24px, 5vw, 120px) 96px;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8f9f7 0%, #fffef6 100%);
	}

	.privacy-content {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
		padding: 60px clamp(32px, 6vw, 80px);
		border-radius: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 24px 48px rgba(31, 42, 28, 0.08);
		backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
	}

	.privacy-content h1 {
		margin: 0 0 16px;
		font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
		font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 48px);
		color: #3a5a40;
		text-align: center;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.last-updated {
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 48px;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: #6b705c;
		font-style: italic;
	}

	.privacy-section {
		margin-bottom: 40px;
	}

	.privacy-section h2 {
		margin: 0 0 20px;
		font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
		font-size: clamp(24px, 4vw, 32px);
		color: #3a5a40;
		border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(58, 90, 64, 0.2);
		padding-bottom: 8px;
	}

	.privacy-section h3 {
		margin: 24px 0 12px;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: #2c4531;
	}

	.privacy-section p {
		margin: 0 0 16px;
		font-size: 16px;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: #424b3a;
	}

	.privacy-section ul {
		margin: 0 0 16px;
		padding-left: 24px;
	}

	.privacy-section li {
		margin: 0 0 8px;
		font-size: 16px;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: #424b3a;
	}

	.privacy-section strong {
		color: #2c4531;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.privacy-section a {
		color: #3a5a40;
		text-decoration: underline;
		transition: color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.privacy-section a:hover {
		color: #2c4531;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.page {
			padding: 100px 24px 60px;
		}

		.privacy-content {
			padding: 40px 24px;
		}

		.privacy-content h1 {
			font-size: clamp(28px, 6vw, 36px);
		}

		.privacy-section h2 {
			font-size: clamp(20px, 5vw, 24px);
		}

		.privacy-section h3 {
			font-size: 16px;
		}

		.privacy-section p,
		.privacy-section li {
			font-size: 15px;
		}
	}
</style>
